<jdudley@eaicorp.com>
[The Chilean advice to vaccinate livestock at the end of the summer is
unusual as anthrax/carbunclo is primarily a hot weather disease in the rest
of the globe. I will check with my Chilean veterinary contacts as to what
they commonly recommend and their usual experiences with this disease. One
of the problems may be that they might have in the past seen outbreaks when
animals were being trailed down from the altiplano pastures to the low
altitude winter pastures, rather as we see in Central Asia. - Mod.MHJ]
