[There are 3 Fresias in Chile -- Punta Capitana comes up on none of my
searches -- and if it is in Biobio go to:
<http://www.fallingrain.com/world/CI/6/Fresia.html>, which is very near the
coast and close to Tome and Rafael, see below.
There are 2 near Osorno in Los Lagos:
<http://www.fallingrain.com/world/CI/9/Fresia2.html>
<http://www.fallingrain.com/world/CI/9/Fresia.html>.
According to OIE, in 2005 there were 5 outbreaks in Chile, with 4 in March
(Araucania (1), Biobio (1), and Los Lagos (2)) and all affecting cattle;
and one Los Lagos outbreak in September 2005, also in cattle. In prior
years there were 3 cattle outbreaks in 2000, 2001 (2), 2002 (4), 2003 (3),
2004 (5); in sheep 2000 (2) and 2004 (1); pigs 2000 (1); and in humans 2000
(9), 2001 (4), 2002 (5), 2003 (4), and 2004 (11). - Mod.MHJ]
